  "text": "There have been attempts at using the compiler to help with early register releasing by indicating the last use of a register. Lo et al. present five schemes for SMT processors that use a mixture of OS and compiler support to relieve register pressure [CITATION_1] . Unfortunately, these schemes do not allow for precise exceptions or interrupts at all either.",
